videos.description: Riley LaChance hits the three from the corner to extend Vanderbilt's lead
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's LaChance nails the three

videos.description: KeVaughn Allen nails a big three from the top of the key as the shot clock runs out
videos.headline: Florida's Allen hits the three at the buzzer

videos.description: Matthew Fisher-Davis hits the three from the top of the key
videos.headline: Fisher-Davis for three!

videos.description: Devin Robinson nails the three to help Florida's comeback
videos.headline: Florida's Robinson for three

videos.description: KeVaughn Allen hits the turnaround three to tie the game 57-57
videos.headline: Florida's Allen with the huge three!

videos.description: Kevarrius Hayes tries for the layup but can't finish, the game goes into OT
videos.headline: Florida can't get it done

videos.description: Nolan Cressler hits the three from the corner
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Cressler nails the three

videos.description: Vanderbilt's Luke Kornet finds Jeff Roberson who flies in for the massive one-handed dunk in the overtime win against Florida.
videos.headline: Roberson with the huge dunk!

videos.description: Vanderbilt head coach Bryce Drew talks about his team's quarterfinal victory over No. 2 seed Florida.
videos.headline: Drew: The resiliency of these guys has been phenomenal

videos.description: Luke Kornet talks about the energy this win took, his hopes for the ending of his senior season, and the next step for Vanderbilt
videos.headline: Postgame Interview with Luke Kornet

videos.description: Riley LaChance puts up five of his 18 points in overtime to propel Vanderbilt past No. 17 Florida 72-62 in the SEC quarterfinals.
videos.headline: Vandy stuns Florida in overtime
